Objective: Refactor a running 20-crate Rust trading terminal (TALON v3.2.0) from its current Hatch-tier state to a fully wired Hatch-tier system where one strategy module (Firebird) generates OrderIntents from live market data, routes them through the supervision gate, and displays everything in TRiMiNL — all on IBKR Gateway paper trading port 4002.
Current state: 20 crates compile clean, 33 tests pass. Three strategy modules have logic (Firebird, Thunderbird, Taxi). The rest are empty scaffolds. Market data flows from Polygon.io (15s poll) + Yahoo Finance (30s fallback) + IBKR historical bars into a DashMap quote cache. The TUI renders. The broker connects. But the full signal-to-order pipeline is not end-to-end wired: strategy modules generate ScanResults, but the path from ScanResult through talon-exec's supervision gate to talon-broker order submission is incomplete.
What needs to happen:

Wire the Firebird module's ScanResult output through talon-exec's supervision gate (G3 hard gate for Hatch tier — every order requires operator approval)
Render pending intents in TRiMiNL with accept/reject keybindings
On operator approval, route the OrderIntent to talon-broker for paper submission
Display fill confirmations in TRiMiNL
Update the Portfolio Bevy Resource on fills
Wire talon-carousel to calculate harvest amount on winning trade closes (log only — no actual transfer in Hatch)

Constraints:

All prices rust_decimal::Decimal, never f64
Strategy crates cannot depend on talon-exec or read Portfolio directly
Communication is bounded channels only (SignalEnvelope in, ExecutionReport out)
Edition 2024, Rust 1.85, openSUSE Tumbleweed
IBKR adapter uses ibapi v2 (already connected, already working)
No Bevy ECS integration yet — that's Takeoff tier. Current architecture uses tokio channels + arc_swap + watch. Don't introduce Bevy now.

